Job Description:
Our CompanyAtheneum Partners is a young and dynamic global expert platform that connects clients with >100,000 top industry specialists to access market intelligence worldwide – covering topics from cocoa plantations in Brazil to high speed trains in Asia to the impact of the Euro Crisis. Our professionals broker knowledge by identifying and recruiting experts to consult clients via phone consultations, surveys, interviews, workshops and custom reports. These discussions provide a comprehensive overview of how market trends, the supply chain, competition, and other factors can impact our clients’ business plans.Atheneum Partners operates in over 30 languages, represents more than 30 nationalities, and has offices in Latin America, Europe, Africa, the Middle East and Asia. The OpportunityDevelop vital skills for any profession: communication, presentation and problem-solvingOpportunity to work on International consulting projects and regular interaction with our offices around the globeRepresent leading expert network in Europe on international scaleMentor program plus solid career progression track for strong performersHuge training and workshops provided Profiles We Are Looking ForBBA, MBA, MS in management with HR, management or consultancy focus preferable Passionate about working in a growing companyAdvanced Internet research skills neededSkilled at researching, investigating and garnering information from internet site resourcesFluent in English and good writing skillsTranscription skills are added advantageTasksIdentify, engage and actively recruit top industry expertsExecute interviews/surveys and generate write-ups/reports to deliver findings to clientsWork in international teams to meet tight project deadlinesDetailed-oriented, with attention to detail for tasks that have zero tolerance for errorsUsing marketing techniques and networking in order to attract business from client companies
